My wife is disabled, she has had one adrenal gland removed and the other one is starting to go bad, which has triggered the diabetes.  She also suffers from super high BP as a result of her adrenal problems.  She had a stroke last November and has little use of her right side, plus it affected her eyesight and now she beginning to get cataracts.  SSI has denied her twice, her doctor has ordered her not to work, and will not even allow her to walk outside.  She has had to get a lawyer.<br>
We are right on the edge if every goes right, will now things have begun to go wrong.  We got cut back on food stamps because of my job, and now today my car's fuel pump may have gone out, which will cost something like $250 to get it fixed, which I need to get fixed because I use the car everynight to make the little money we get.  But I do not have it, and I do not know what we are going to do.  If I lose this job, there will be no cash to have a roof over our heads.<br>
Does anyone have any ideas of what I could do?  I am at my wits end now.  This month I also have a 92 dollar car insurance bill that is due.<br>
A couple of years ago when we moved into this trailer, both of us were working full time as Certified Nurses Aides.  My wife lost her job because of health last summer, and in Dec of 2001 I was <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://mywebpage.netscape.com/jeffnymanCNA/index.htm" target="top">fired.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Jeff the Finn <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/nban44.JPG" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0> at: 8/14/03 12:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heartjoys>heartjoys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Velvet-Steel Wannabe</span><br>  Posts: 998<br> <font color=#B87333>(8/14/03 6:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/CladdaghAward.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: asking for prayer</span><hr size=1> Oh, what a shock to read this Jeff.  I am so sorry that you and your wife are dealing with SO much right now.  Of course I will be praying for you.<br>
<br>
I know how it feels to be overwhelmed by circumstances, so I hope you will make the time to just be still before God and take one issue at a time.<br>
<br>
Do you have a friend that you could loan a vehicle to you and/or take a look at your fuel pump at least to verify this IS the problem before taking it to a garage?<br>
<br>
With your skills as a CNA, are there any programs in Oregon that make use of your skills for home visits to patients?  There is always a need for these folks here in WV-- they may work with the nurses, I don't know.  You have valuable skills and especially working with the elderly; I hope you may be able to find a way to use those gifts and skills in another way apart from nursing homes. <br>
<br>
Didn't I read somewhere that you are an English tutor?  or teacher?  Do you have a way that you might offer your help for college or high school students?  Also, apparently, from your participation here, you have valuable computer skills/graphic design, you might be able to use those skills in your area too, or even through a job related to developing websites.<br>
<br>
Hang in there; I'll be praying for you.<br>
